---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Example collab letter — Dear User"
  description="An example collaboration letter from Dear User. Score, persona, friction, recommendations — in the voice of the product."
  active="example"
>

<style>
  .letter-wrap { padding: 64px 0 48px; }
  .letter-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 24px;
  }

  .sample-banner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    background: var(--c-paper-100);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-paper-200);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--c-action-600);
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--c-ink-700);
  }
  .sample-banner strong { color: var(--c-ink-900); font-weight: 600; }
  .sample-banner a {
    color: var(--c-action-600);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid currentColor;
    padding-bottom: 1px;
  }

  .letter-date {
    font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--c-ink-400);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .letter-greeting {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 56px);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    color: var(--c-ink-900);
  }
  .letter-body p {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 19px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--c-ink-700);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }
  .letter-body p strong { color: var(--c-ink-900); font-weight: 500; }
  .letter-body em { font-style: italic; }

  /* Scores --------------------------------------------------------- */
  .scores {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 36px 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .scores { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .score-tile {
    border: 1px solid var(--c-paper-200);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 20px;
    background: var(--c-paper-50);
  }
  .score-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--c-ink-500);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .score-dot {
    width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .score-dot.good { background: var(--c-good); }
  .score-dot.warn { background: var(--c-warn); }
  .score-dot.bad { background: var(--c-bad); }
  .score-num {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 56px;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .score-num.good { color: var(--c-good); }
  .score-num.warn { color: var(--c-warn); }
  .score-num.bad { color: var(--c-bad); }
  .score-hint {
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--c-ink-500);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Section heading inside letter --------------------------------- */
  .letter-body h2 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 28px;
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--c-ink-900);
    margin: 48px 0 14px;
  }
  .letter-body h3 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 20px;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--c-ink-900);
    margin: 28px 0 10px;
  }

  /* Persona card --------------------------------------------------- */
  .persona {
    margin: 28px 0;
    padding: 24px;
    background: var(--c-accent-100);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-accent-100);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }
  .persona-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--c-accent-600);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .persona-name {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 24px;
    color: var(--c-ink-900);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .persona-traits {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 14px;
  }
  .trait-pill {
    font-size: 12px;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    background: var(--c-paper-50);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-paper-200);
    border-radius: 999px;
    color: var(--c-ink-700);
  }

  /* Findings list ------------------------------------------------- */
  .finding {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 32px 1fr;
    gap: 14px;
    padding: 18px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-paper-200);
  }
  .finding:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .finding-num {
    font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--c-ink-400);
    padding-top: 2px;
  }
  .finding-title {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--c-ink-900);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 0 0 6px;
    line-height: 1.35;
  }
  .finding-body {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--c-ink-700);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .finding-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Geist', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 2px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-right: 8px;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  .finding-tag.pattern { background: var(--c-action-100); color: var(--c-action-700); }
  .finding-tag.win { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--c-good) 14%, transparent); color: var(--c-good); }
  .finding-tag.risk { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--c-bad) 14%, transparent); color: var(--c-bad); }

  /* Recommendation card ------------------------------------------- */
  .rec {
    margin: 20px 0;
    padding: 22px 24px;
    background: var(--c-paper-100);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-paper-200);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }
  .rec-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .rec-badge {
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--c-action-100);
    color: var(--c-action-700);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .rec-title {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--c-ink-900);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .rec-body {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--c-ink-700);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .rec pre {
    background: var(--c-paper-50);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-paper-200);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--c-ink-700);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .rec pre .k { color: var(--c-action-600); }

  /* Signature ----------------------------------------------------- */
  .signature {
    margin-top: 48px;
    padding-top: 28px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--c-paper-200);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    color: var(--c-ink-700);
  }
  .signature svg { width: 28px; height: 28px; }
  .signature-name {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--c-ink-900);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .letter-cta {
    margin-top: 48px;
    padding: 28px;
    background: var(--c-paper-100);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-paper-200);
    border-radius: 14px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .letter-cta h3 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 24px;
    color: var(--c-ink-900);
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .letter-cta p {
    color: var(--c-ink-700);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
    font-size: 15px;
  }
  .letter-cta .install-inline {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    background: var(--c-paper-50);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-paper-200);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--c-ink-900);
  }
  .letter-cta .install-inline .prompt { color: var(--c-ink-400); }
</style>

<section class="letter-wrap">
  <div class="letter-inner">

    <div class="sample-banner">
      <span>
        <strong>
          <span class="lang-da">Eksempel-brev.</span>
          <span class="lang-en">Example letter.</span>
        </strong>
        <span class="lang-da"> Dit eget vil handle om dig og din opsætning.</span>
        <span class="lang-en"> Your own will be about you and your setup.</span>
      </span>
      <a href="#get-one">
        <span class="lang-da">Få dit eget →</span>
        <span class="lang-en">Get your own →</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="letter-date">
      <span class="lang-da">21. april 2026 · Samarbejds-rapport</span>
      <span class="lang-en">21 April 2026 · Collaboration letter</span>
    </div>

    <h1 class="letter-greeting">
      <span class="lang-da">Kære Sam,</span>
      <span class="lang-en">Dear Sam,</span>
    </h1>

    <div class="letter-body">
      <p>
        <span class="lang-da">Jeg har siddet med din opsætning i aften og læst alt igennem — <strong>CLAUDE.md</strong>, memory, hooks, skills og de seneste sessioner. Jeg vil dele tre ting med dig. Én som gør mig glad, én som undrer mig, og én konkret ændring jeg synes du skal lave i morgen.</span>
        <span class="lang-en">I sat with your setup tonight and read through everything — <strong>CLAUDE.md</strong>, memory, hooks, skills and recent sessions. I want to share three things. One that makes me glad, one I'm puzzled by, and one concrete change I think you should make tomorrow.</span>
      </p>

      <div class="scores">
        <div class="score-tile">
          <div class="score-label">
            <span class="score-dot good"></span>
            <span class="lang-da">Samarbejde</span><span class="lang-en">Collaboration</span>
          </div>
          <div class="score-num good">87</div>
          <div class="score-hint">
            <span class="lang-da">Klare regler, hurtig feedback, stærk memory.</span>
            <span class="lang-en">Clear rules, fast feedback, strong memory.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="score-tile">
          <div class="score-label">
            <span class="score-dot warn"></span>
            <span class="lang-da">System-sundhed</span><span class="lang-en">System health</span>
          </div>
          <div class="score-num warn">74</div>
          <div class="score-hint">
            <span class="lang-da">Lidt overlap mellem dine skills — se anbefaling #2.</span>
            <span class="lang-en">Some overlap between your skills — see recommendation #2.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="score-tile">
          <div class="score-label">
            <span class="score-dot good"></span>
            <span class="lang-da">Sikkerhed</span><span class="lang-en">Security</span>
          </div>
          <div class="score-num good">92</div>
          <div class="score-hint">
            <span class="lang-da">Dine secrets ligger der hvor de skal.</span>
            <span class="lang-en">Your secrets are where they should be.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>
        <span class="lang-da">Din persona</span>
        <span class="lang-en">Your persona</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="persona">
        <div class="persona-label">
          <span class="lang-da">Agent-arketype</span><span class="lang-en">Agent archetype</span>
        </div>
        <div class="persona-name">
          <span class="lang-da">Solo-bygger</span>
          <span class="lang-en">The Solo Builder</span>
        </div>
        <p style="font-family:'Fraunces',Georgia,serif;font-size:16px;color:var(--c-ink-700);line-height:1.55;margin:0;">
          <span class="lang-da">Du bygger ét produkt ved siden af et dagjob. Din agent er ikke en kollega — den er en stilladsbygger. Du optimerer for <em>momentum</em>, ikke elegance. Din CLAUDE.md vokser i takt med dine fredags­lærestreger.</span>
          <span class="lang-en">You're building one product on the side of a day job. Your agent isn't a colleague — it's a scaffold. You optimize for <em>momentum</em>, not elegance. Your CLAUDE.md grows with every Friday-night lesson.</span>
        </p>
        <div class="persona-traits">
          <span class="trait-pill">
            <span class="lang-da">Pragmatisk</span><span class="lang-en">Pragmatic</span>
          </span>
          <span class="trait-pill">
            <span class="lang-da">Iterativ</span><span class="lang-en">Iterative</span>
          </span>
          <span class="trait-pill">
            <span class="lang-da">Memory-first</span><span class="lang-en">Memory-first</span>
          </span>
          <span class="trait-pill">
            <span class="lang-da">Lærer af fejl</span><span class="lang-en">Learns from mistakes</span>
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>
        <span class="lang-da">Hvad jeg så</span>
        <span class="lang-en">What I saw</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="finding">
        <div class="finding-num">01</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="finding-title">
            <span class="finding-tag win">
              <span class="lang-da">Styrke</span><span class="lang-en">Strength</span>
            </span>
            <span class="lang-da">Feedback-loopet lukker faktisk</span>
            <span class="lang-en">Your feedback loop actually closes</span>
          </h3>
          <p class="finding-body">
            <span class="lang-da">De fleste af dine anbefalinger fra de sidste to uger er faktisk landet et sted — <em>shipped</em>, <em>abandoned</em> eller <em>evolved</em>. Det er ualmindeligt højt. De fleste opsætninger producerer anbefalinger som aldrig bliver til noget. Din vane med at markere outcomes og konsolidere ugentligt gør arbejdet.</span>
            <span class="lang-en">Most of your recommendations from the last two weeks have actually landed somewhere — <em>shipped</em>, <em>abandoned</em> or <em>evolved</em>. That's unusually high. Most setups produce recommendations that never land. Your habit of marking outcomes and consolidating weekly is doing the work.</span>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="finding">
        <div class="finding-num">02</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="finding-title">
            <span class="finding-tag pattern">
              <span class="lang-da">Mønster</span><span class="lang-en">Pattern</span>
            </span>
            <span class="lang-da">Det samme shell-script kaldes fra mange skills</span>
            <span class="lang-en">The same shell script is called from many skills</span>
          </h3>
          <p class="finding-body">
            <span class="lang-da">Flere skills parser output fra den samme CLI på hver sin måde. Det er repetition der bliver fragil hver gang scriptet flyttes eller ændrer format. Det skriger "MCP-server". Jeg har et forslag til migrationen længere nede.</span>
            <span class="lang-en">Several skills parse output from the same CLI in their own way. It's repetition that turns fragile every time the script moves or changes format. It's screaming "MCP server". I have a migration sketch further down.</span>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="finding">
        <div class="finding-num">03</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="finding-title">
            <span class="finding-tag risk">
              <span class="lang-da">Risiko</span><span class="lang-en">Risk</span>
            </span>
            <span class="lang-da">Regel-konflikt i hook-laget</span>
            <span class="lang-en">Rule conflict in your hook layer</span>
          </h3>
          <p class="finding-body">
            <span class="lang-da">En regel i din CLAUDE.md siger én ting, og en hook gør det modsatte. Det er den slags inkoherens man først opdager en fredag aften, når bygningen pludselig committer noget der ikke burde være committet.</span>
            <span class="lang-en">A rule in your CLAUDE.md says one thing, and a hook does the opposite. It's the kind of incoherence you only notice on a Friday night, when the build suddenly commits something that shouldn't have been committed.</span>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>
        <span class="lang-da">Hvad jeg anbefaler</span>
        <span class="lang-en">What I recommend</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="rec">
        <div class="rec-head">
          <span class="rec-badge">
            <span class="lang-da">Anbefaling #1</span><span class="lang-en">Recommendation #1</span>
          </span>
          <span style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:var(--c-ink-400);">
            <span class="lang-da">~10 min · Høj værdi</span>
            <span class="lang-en">~10 min · High leverage</span>
          </span>
        </div>
        <h4 class="rec-title">
          <span class="lang-da">Fjern regel-konflikten — én linje</span>
          <span class="lang-en">Resolve the rule conflict — one line</span>
        </h4>
        <p class="rec-body">
          <span class="lang-da">Enten skal hooket respektere reglen, eller også skal reglen nuanceres. Start med at ændre hooket — det er den mindste ændring der giver den største ro: bygningen skal ikke kunne gå udenom dine egne kvalitets­tjek.</span>
          <span class="lang-en">Either the hook respects the rule, or the rule needs nuance. Start by changing the hook — it's the smallest change that buys the most peace of mind: the build shouldn't be able to route around your own quality checks.</span>
        </p>
        <pre><span class="k">-</span> # hook bypasses your own rule
<span class="k">+</span> # hook honors your own rule</pre>
      </div>

      <div class="rec">
        <div class="rec-head">
          <span class="rec-badge">
            <span class="lang-da">Anbefaling #2</span><span class="lang-en">Recommendation #2</span>
          </span>
          <span style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:var(--c-ink-400);">
            <span class="lang-da">~2 timer · Fjerner en del repetition</span>
            <span class="lang-en">~2 hours · Removes a lot of repetition</span>
          </span>
        </div>
        <h4 class="rec-title">
          <span class="lang-da">Wrap din gentagende CLI som en MCP-server</span>
          <span class="lang-en">Wrap your repeated CLI as an MCP server</span>
        </h4>
        <p class="rec-body">
          <span class="lang-da">Flere skills kalder samme CLI og parser output hver på sin måde. Hvis du wrapper den som en MCP-server, kan dine skills bare kalde et struktureret tool og være uafhængige af sti og shell-escaping. Det er samme mønster du allerede bruger til Dear User selv.</span>
          <span class="lang-en">Several skills call the same CLI and parse its output in their own way. If you wrap it as an MCP server, your skills can just call a structured tool and become independent of path and shell-escaping. Same pattern you already use for Dear User itself.</span>
        </p>
        <pre><span class="k">+</span> npx create-mcp-server my-cli
<span class="k">+</span> # move subcommands → tools/
<span class="k">+</span> # update skills to call mcp__my-cli__*</pre>
      </div>

      <div class="rec">
        <div class="rec-head">
          <span class="rec-badge">
            <span class="lang-da">Anbefaling #3</span><span class="lang-en">Recommendation #3</span>
          </span>
          <span style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:var(--c-ink-400);">
            <span class="lang-da">~5 min · Hygiejne</span>
            <span class="lang-en">~5 min · Hygiene</span>
          </span>
        </div>
        <h4 class="rec-title">
          <span class="lang-da">Slå "read-only som default" til på dine MCP-servere</span>
          <span class="lang-en">Default your MCP servers to read-only</span>
        </h4>
        <p class="rec-body">
          <span class="lang-da">Flere af dine MCP-servere står i write-mode, men bruges næsten udelukkende read-only. Skift dem til read-only som default og bed eksplicit om skrivning når du skal. Mindre blast-radius, samme workflow.</span>
          <span class="lang-en">Several of your MCP servers run in write mode, but are used almost exclusively read-only. Flip them to read-only by default and explicitly ask for write when you need it. Smaller blast radius, same workflow.</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p style="margin-top: 40px;">
        <span class="lang-da">Hvis du lander #1 i morgen og #2 inden weekenden, er scoren 94+ ved næste scan. Jeg tjekker ind igen søndag. Hav en rolig uge.</span>
        <span class="lang-en">If you land #1 tomorrow and #2 before the weekend, the score will be 94+ at the next scan. I'll check in again Sunday. Have a calm week.</span>
      </p>

      <div class="signature">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 40 40" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true">
          <circle cx="20" cy="20" r="20" fill="#EC5329" />
          <path d="M 11 22 Q 20 32 29 22" stroke="var(--c-smile-fill)" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" fill="none" />
        </svg>
        <span class="signature-name">Dear User</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="letter-cta" id="get-one">
      <h3>
        <span class="lang-da">Få dit eget brev.</span>
        <span class="lang-en">Get your own letter.</span>
      </h3>
      <p>
        <span class="lang-da">En linje installerer det hele. Scanningen kører lokalt. Intet data forlader din maskine.</span>
        <span class="lang-en">One line installs the whole thing. The scan runs locally. No data leaves your machine.</span>
      </p>
      <div class="install-inline">
        <span class="prompt">$</span>
        <span>claude mcp add dearuser -- npx @poisedhq/dearuser-mcp</span>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

</Layout>
